-- BoA hires new Asia, EMEA head for rates, FX sales
-- 
-- Sun Jan 24, 2010 10:22pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/01/25/us-bank-am-appointment-idUSTRE60O0CT20100125

 

 HONG KONG  (Reuters) - Bank of America Merrill Lynch ( BAC.N ) has appointed Vinit Sahni as head of Asia and EMEA flow rates and currencies sales and the global head of hedge fund and central banks sales for rates and currencies, it said. 

 Vinit's earlier stints were with Goldman Sachs ( GS.N ), Deutsche Bank ( DBKGn.DE ) and Soros Fund Management, it said in a statement on Monday. (Reporting by Saikat Chatterjee; Editing by  Jonathan Hopfner )